    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-11-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="29"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C114/584</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Assistant Chief of the Division of Western European Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Richardson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-11-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1926</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Richardson</hi>: I have read the attached
                    memorandum on the World Court.<note n="36" xml:id="d29fn36">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> As I remember, I looked it up last year
                    with Senator Pepper, Mr. Lenroot and others and, under the Resolution of the
                    Senate, we cannot sign the Protocol until every nation signatory to the original
                    Statute of the World Court has accepted the reservations. It does not make any
                    difference whether they ratified it by their Congress, Senate or other body.
                    There is no use of communicating with the governments that have accepted. Every
                    one of them must accept or we cannot join and the President will in no way
                    recommend any change in the situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">rank</hi>] B. K[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ellogg</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
